sentences: Ralph Winston Morris (born January 19, 1941 in Barnwell, South Carolina) is an American tubist.
Morris earned his academic degree in music from East Carolina University in 1962.
As the conductor of the Tennessee Tech Tuba Ensemble, he started promoting jazz tuba performance in an ensemble setting as early as 1967.
A recent reunion concert billed as Tubas of Mass Destruction, held in 2007 at Tennessee Tech University, included over 100 current and former students from his 40 years of teaching.
Morris created and now conducts Symphonia, a tuba/euphonium ensemble made up of professional players.
A recent reunion concert billed as Tubas of Mass Destruction, held in 2007 at Tennessee Tech University, included over 100 current and former students from his 40 years of teaching.

Throughout his teaching career, Morris has encouraged his students to arrange and compose pieces of music for the ensemble, which was necessary in the early days of the group as there was virtually no repertoire for them to play.
